Dear Rafaella,
Thank you for your email.
As Megan mentioned in her response on 15 September 2025, the additional inf=
ormation you requested will be provided by 8 October 2025.
Regarding the fees: we can only provide an estimate if you agree for us to =
proceed with the additional work, which includes indexing by date, author, =
short description, and system/location.
We will also review the redactions made and assess what can be done to meet=
 your request.
Warm regards
[cid:image001.png@01DC2EBB.F688BA30]
Privacy Team
Level 5, 136 Fanshawe Street,
PO Box 90347, Auckland 1142
[Text  Description automatically generated with low confidence]
Fair Insurance Code
Tower is a member of the Insurance Council of New Zealand (ICNZ).
We abide by the ICNZ Fair Insurance Code<https://www.icnz.org.nz/fair-insur=
ance-code/>.

Tower holds a Financial Advice Provider licence, issued by the Financial Ma=
rkets Authority.
Our Nominated Representatives may provide financial advice on insurance pro=
ducts provided by Tower.
Tower Insurance is a member of the Insurance and Financial Services Ombudsm=
an Scheme.
Please click here<https://www.tower.co.nz/about-us/publicly-available-discl=
osure/> for our publicly available disclosure document.
Privacy Disclaimer: This email and its attachments are confidential. If you=
 are not the intended recipient,
please notify the sender and delete this email. Unauthorised use or disclos=
ure is prohibited.
Tower Insurance takes your privacy seriously. For more information, please =
refer to our Privacy Statement.<https://www.tower.co.nz/terms-and-condition=
s/>



Classification: Sensitive
From: Raffaella del Prete <raffaellanz@icloud.com>
Sent: Thursday, 25 September 2025 5:45 pm
To: Privacy <Privacy@tower.co.nz>
Cc: Megan Jensen <Megan.Jensen@tower.co.nz>; Lance O'Riley <Lance.ORiley@to=
wer.co.nz>
Subject: Re: Privacy Request
Importance: High

Kia ora, Thank you for your response and for the documents provided. Having=
 reviewed the material so far, it still appears incomplete and not up to da=
te. Could you please: 1) ETA for full disclosure Provide an ETA for when th=
e full file will

Kia ora,

Thank you for your response and for the documents provided. Having reviewed=
 the material so far, it still appears incomplete and not up to date. Could=
 you please:

1) ETA for full disclosure
Provide an ETA for when the full file will be shared, including all materia=
l identified in your =E2=80=9Centerprise-wide search.=E2=80=9D If rolling d=
isclosure is being used, please confirm what further releases I should expe=
ct and by when.

2) Fees
Please confirm that no fees will be charged for this request. Given this re=
quest arises from Tower=E2=80=99s own system handling and relates to my per=
sonal information, I consider fees inappropriate.  If Tower still intends t=
o impose fees, please provide a written bill/estimate in advance detailing =
the calculation (time, hourly rate, and scope of work).

By way of reassurance, I am a professional in IT and experienced with insur=
ance systems. I would be happy to review the search approach to ensure the =
search is both appropriate and efficient, and to avoid unnecessary duplicat=
ion or administrative burden.

3) Redactions
Redactions to date appear to extend beyond simple removal of other people=
=E2=80=99s names and personal identifiers. Please confirm the specific lega=
l grounds relied upon for each redaction or withholding, and explain why pa=
rtial release was not reasonably practicable. Where =E2=80=9Ccommercial sen=
sitivity=E2=80=9D is claimed, I ask that non-sensitive technical content an=
d valuation inputs (scope descriptions, quantities, allowances, rates, cont=
ingencies) still be disclosed, as these are required for transparency and f=
airness in assessing my claim.

Ng=C4=81 mihi,
Raffaella


On 25 Sep 2025, at 1:01=E2=80=AFPM, Privacy <Privacy@tower.co.nz<mailto:Pri=
vacy@tower.co.nz>> wrote:

Kia ora Rafaella,

Thank you for your detailed email and for raising these concerns. I want to=
 acknowledge the stress and frustration this situation has caused, especial=
ly given the circumstances you're already navigating following the fire. We=
 take your concerns seriously and are committed to addressing them thorough=
ly and respectfully.

A) Security / Containment
We sincerely apologise for the oversight regarding the link access. We have=
 now:

  *   Disabled the current ShareFile link.
  *   Initiated a reissue of access that is restricted and tied solely to y=
our email address. https://towernz.sharefile.com/d-sb3797728cdc745088741e36=
a60cdfbe1 [towernz.sharefile.com]<https://urldefense.com/v3/__https:/towern=
z.sharefile.com/d-sb3797728cdc745088741e36a60cdfbe1__;!!NPvfczxIteVBjg!AVYt=
EjQ8mHMqoFnPEKGMVdepnpgqPwlpGXqwGdB_c__-ag19JJWSVWsliQ2qKr_bYN42jSjTXsE9PSF=
k-IrVVCVN$>
  *   A full audit log from ShareFile, including activity, and access event=
s. This has been uploaded to your file.
We have used the Privacy Commissioners =E2=80=9CNotifyUs=E2=80=9D tool as r=
equested on 15 September to review whether this incident meets the threshol=
d for a notifiable privacy breach under the Privacy Act. We confirm the out=
come of that assessment return being unlikely event, due to that Tower can =
see who has access to the link and the link has only been shared to yoursel=
f. The report is also included in your file in the link.

B) Substantive Privacy Act Response
We acknowledge your original request and the legal entitlements under IPP6 =
of the Privacy Act 2020. We are now conducting a fresh, enterprise-wide sea=
rch across all relevant systems and third-party providers to ensure complet=
eness. This includes:

  *   Internal communications (email, IM, call logs, transcripts)
  *   Third-party instructions and correspondence
  *   Site media and technical reports
  *   ShareFile configuration and access logs. Already included.

However, we won=E2=80=99t be providing a document index for this privacy re=
quest, as creating one would be a significant administrative task and isn=
=E2=80=99t something we=E2=80=99re required to do under the Privacy Act. Th=
e Act requires us to provide access to existing personal information, but n=
ot to create new documents or indexes. We=E2=80=99d also like to note that =
if a request is particularly detailed or requires a lot of extra work to pr=
ocess, we are entitled to charge a reasonable fee to cover the administrati=
ve costs involved.

Grounds for any redactions or withholdings, however, some documents have be=
en withheld or redacted because they contain the personal information of ot=
her individuals, which we are legally required to protect under the Privacy=
 Act. Additionally, certain documents include commercially sensitive inform=
ation=E2=80=94such as contractor pricing or internal business processes, th=
at cannot be disclosed. We understand this may be disappointing, and we=E2=
=80=99re committed to being as transparent as possible within those legal a=
nd commercial boundaries. This said, we will provide more detail where we c=
an on the specific redactions.

C) Records Preservation
We confirm that all records relating to your claims are being preserved unt=
il both matters are fully resolved and all requested documentation has been=
 provided.

We appreciate your patience and your clear articulation of the issues. Plea=
se know that we are treating this with urgency and care, and we are committ=
ed to resolving it directly with you.

Warm regards
<image001.png>
Johann Engelbrecht
Compliance and Privacy Advisor
Level 5, 136 Fanshawe Street,
PO Box 90347, Auckland 1142
<image002.png>
